def binary_encoding(df):
  """Encodes all columns with binary notation t and f"""
  for columns in df:
    df.replace({'f': 0,'t': 1}, inplace=True) # encoding binary variables
  return df

In [27]:
# Conversion rates to USD
rates = {'Paris': 1.06,
         'Sydney': 0.64,
         'Rome': 1.06,
         'New York': 1.00,
         'Rio de Janeiro': 0.19,
         'Istanbul': 0.03,
         'Mexico City': 0.05,
         'Bangkok':0.02,
         'Cape Town':0.05,
         'Hong Kong': 0.13}

# Convert prices to USD
df['price_converted'] = df['price']
for city, rate in rates.items():
    df.loc[df['city'] == city, 'price_converted'] = df.loc[df['city'] == city, 'price'] * rate

# Prices in USD
df.drop('price', axis=1, inplace=True)
In [31]:
def encode_city(city):
  city_dict = {'Paris': 1,'Sydney': 2,'Rome': 3,'New York': 4,'Rio de Janeiro': 5,
               'Istanbul': 6,'Mexico City': 7,'Bangkok': 8,'Cape Town': 9,'Hong Kong': 10}

  return city_dict[city]

df['city_value'] = df['city'].apply(encode_city)

# multiple ttests of room_type pairs to investigate significance in price difference

alpha=0.01  #significance level

res_1 = scipy.stats.ttest_ind(df1, df2)
if res_1.pvalue < alpha:
  print('Private room vs Entire home/apt p-value: {:.10f}'.format(ttest_ind(df1, df2).pvalue))
res_2= scipy.stats.ttest_ind(df1, df3)
if res_2.pvalue < alpha:
  print('Private room vs Hotel room p-value: {:.10f}'.format(ttest_ind(df1, df3).pvalue))
res_3= scipy.stats.ttest_ind(df1, df4)
if res_3.pvalue < alpha:
  print('Private room vs Shared room: {:.10f}'.format(ttest_ind(df1, df4).pvalue))
res_4= scipy.stats.ttest_ind(df2, df3)
if res_4.pvalue < alpha:
  print('Entire home/apt vs Hotel room p-value: {:.10f}'.format(ttest_ind(df2, df3).pvalue))
res_5= scipy.stats.ttest_ind(df2, df4)
if res_5.pvalue < alpha:
  print('Entire home/apt vs Shared room p-value: {:.10f}'.format(ttest_ind(df2, df4).pvalue))
res_6= scipy.stats.ttest_ind(df3, df4)
if res_6.pvalue < alpha:
  print('Hotel room  vs Shared room p-value: {:.10f}'.format(ttest_ind(df3, df4).pvalue))

#Bonferroni correction to compensate for any bias as a result of multiple hypothesis testing

alpha=0.01   # initial significance level
no_test= 6   # number of hypothesis
Threshold=alpha/no_test     # new significance level


res_1 = scipy.stats.ttest_ind(df1, df2)
if res_1.pvalue < Threshold:
  print('Private room vs Entire home/apt p-value: {:.10f}'.format(ttest_ind(df1, df2).pvalue))
res_2= scipy.stats.ttest_ind(df1, df3)
if res_2.pvalue < Threshold:
  print('Private room vs Hotel room p-value: {:.10f}'.format(ttest_ind(df1, df3).pvalue))
res_3= scipy.stats.ttest_ind(df1, df4)
if res_3.pvalue < Threshold:
  print('Private room vs Shared room: {:.10f}'.format(ttest_ind(df1, df4).pvalue))
res_4= scipy.stats.ttest_ind(df2, df3)
if res_4.pvalue < Threshold:
  print('Entire home/apt vs Hotel room p-value: {:.10f}'.format(ttest_ind(df2, df3).pvalue))

if res_5.pvalue < Threshold:
  print('Entire home/apt vs Shared room p-value: {:.10f}'.format(ttest_ind(df2, df4).pvalue))

import math

print("Welcome to the Airbnb Price Recommender!")

min_host_listings = 0.0
max_host_listings = 1337.0
min_host_verified = 0.0
max_host_verified = 1.0
min_accommodates = 1
max_accommodates = 16
min_bedrooms = 1.0
max_bedrooms = 20.0
min_nights = 1
max_nights = 9999
min_review_rating = 20.0
max_review_rating = 100.0
min_cleanliness = 2.0
max_cleanliness = 10.0
min_communication = 2.0
max_communication = 10.0
min_location = 2.0
max_location = 10.0
min_value = 2.0
max_value = 10.0
min_city = 1
max_city = 10

cities = {'Paris': 1,'Sydney': 2,'Rome': 3,'New York': 4,'Rio de Janeiro': 5,
          'Istanbul': 6,'Mexico City': 7,'Bangkok': 8,'Cape Town': 9,'Hong Kong': 10}

while True:
  host_listings = float(input("Enter host total listings count (between "+str(min_host_listings)+" and "+str(max_host_listings)+"): "))
  if host_listings < min_host_listings or host_listings > max_host_listings:
    print("Input out of range, please try again.")
    continue

  host_verified = float(input("Enter 1 if host is verified, 0 if not (between "+str(min_host_verified)+" and "+str(max_host_verified)+"): "))
  if host_verified < min_host_verified or host_verified > max_host_verified:
    print("Input out of range, please try again.")
    continue

  accommodates = int(input("Enter number of guests accommodated (between "+str(min_accommodates)+" and "+str(max_accommodates)+"): "))
  if accommodates < min_accommodates or accommodates > max_accommodates:
    print("Input out of range, please try again.")
    continue

  bedrooms = float(input("Enter number of bedrooms (between "+str(min_bedrooms)+" and "+str(max_bedrooms)+"): "))
  if bedrooms < min_bedrooms or bedrooms > max_bedrooms:
    print("Input out of range, please try again.")
    continue

  nights = int(input("Enter minimum number of nights (between "+str(min_nights)+" and "+str(max_nights)+"): "))
  if nights < min_nights or nights > max_nights:
    print("Input out of range, please try again.")
    continue

  rating = float(input("Enter review score rating (between "+str(min_review_rating)+" and "+str(max_review_rating)+"): "))
  if rating < min_review_rating or rating > max_review_rating:
    print("Input out of range, please try again.")
    continue

  cleanliness = float(input("Enter cleanliness score (between "+str(min_cleanliness)+" and "+str(max_cleanliness)+"): "))
  if cleanliness < min_cleanliness or cleanliness > max_cleanliness:
    print("Input out of range, please try again.")
    continue

  communication = float(input("Enter communication score (between "+str(min_communication)+" and "+str(max_communication)+"): "))
  if communication < min_communication or communication > max_communication:
    print("Input out of range, please try again.")
    continue

  location = float(input("Enter location score (between "+str(min_location)+" and "+str(max_location)+"): "))
  if location < min_location or location > max_location:
    print("Input out of range, please try again.")
    continue

  value = float(input("Enter value score (between "+str(min_value)+" and "+str(max_value)+"): "))
  if value < min_value or value > max_value:
    print("Input out of range, please try again.")
    continue

  city = input("Enter city (Paris, Sydney, Rome, etc.): ")
  if city not in cities:
    print("Invalid city, please try again.")
    continue

  city_value = cities[city]

  intercept = 27.7725
  host_listings_coef = 10.9801
  bedrooms_coef = 49.8700
  city_coef = -10.1793
  cleanliness_coef = 7.7411
  communication_coef = -10.8532
  host_verified_coef = 12.4286
  host_listings_cnt_coef = 0.1016
  location_coef = 10.8153
  nights_coef = 0.5527
  rating_coef = 1.3888
  value_coef = -15.4222
  constant = 8333

  price = (intercept +
          host_listings_coef * host_listings +
          bedrooms_coef * bedrooms +
          city_coef * city_value +
          cleanliness_coef * cleanliness +
          communication_coef * communication +
          host_verified_coef * host_verified +
          host_listings_cnt_coef * host_listings +
          location_coef * location +
          nights_coef * nights +
          rating_coef * rating +
          value_coef * value)

  price = math.ceil(price)

  print("The suggested price for your new Airbnb listing based on your inputs is $" + str(price))

  break
